<item>
            <title>[DERBY-3194] LOCALIZEDDISPLAY of CURRENT_TIMESTAMP returns only the TIME</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3194</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In IJ - LOCALIZEDDISPLAY ON causes  VALUES CURRENT_TIMESTAMP to display on the TIME&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ij&amp;gt; values current_timestamp;&lt;br/&gt;
1&lt;br/&gt;
--------------------------&lt;br/&gt;
2007-11-09 10:37:58.828&lt;br/&gt;
1 row selected&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ij&amp;gt; localizeddisplay on;&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; values current_timestamp;&lt;br/&gt;
1&lt;br/&gt;
---------------&lt;br/&gt;
10:38:10 AM PST&lt;br/&gt;
1 row selected&lt;/p&gt;</description>
